First Lady Jill Biden delivered a speech at the White House, emphasizing the importance of art in our lives. She mentioned how art stops us in our tracks and feeds our spirit, showing the contours of our sorrows and joys. The First Lady congratulated the recipients of the art prize and highlighted the power of art to bring people together and transcend borders and time. She expressed gratitude to members of the Cabinet and other dignitaries in attendance, including Secretary Haaland, Ambassador Tai, Representatives Pallone and Matsui, and Secretary Clinton. The First Lady also thanked Mr. Hieda and the Ambassadors from Japan for joining the event and mentioned the strong friendship between the United States and Japan. She concluded her speech by acknowledging the role of art in connecting people and cultures.